s order, cleric, clergyman’. As all writing and secretarial work in medieval Christian Europe was normally done by members of the clergy, the term <i>clerk</i> came to mean ‘scholar, secretary, recorder, or penman’ as well as ‘cleric’. As a surname, it was particularly common for one who had taken only minor holy orders. In medieval Christian Europe, clergy in minor orders were permitted to marry and so found families; thus the surname could become established.","Irish (Westmeath, Mayo): in Ireland the English surname was frequently adopted, partly by translation for <i>Ó Cléirigh</i>; see   Cleary  .","Americanized form of Dutch   De Klerk   or Flemish   De Clerck   or of variants of these names, and possibly also of French   Clerc  . Compare   Clerk   2 and   De Clark  ."]},{"name":"Clarkston","meanings":["English (Nottinghamshire): variant of   Clarkson   with intrusive <i>-t-</i>. The name is not from Clarkston (Lanarkshire, Renfrewshire), which are recent places with names containing the surname   Clark  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Clarkson was born in 1470, in Middleton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with William Rugeley. She died after 1510."},"et":{"1470–after 1510":"1470–pärast 1510","1461–1510":"1461–1510","1486–1558":"1486–1558","1490–1554":"1490–1554","1511–1581":"1511–1581","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1558":"1558","1511":"1511","1554":"1554","1510":"1510","1486":"1486","about 1511":"umbes 1511","1461":"1461","1581":"1581","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","after 1510":"pärast 1510","England":"England","Shenstone, Staffordshire, England":"Shenstone, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Middleton, Warwickshire, England":"Middleton, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1470–after 1510":"1470–1510 jälkeen","1461–1510":"1461–1510","1486–1558":"1486–1558","1490–1554":"1490–1554","1511–1581":"1511–1581","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1558":"1558","1511":"1511","1554":"1554","1510":"1510","1486":"1486","about 1511":"noin 1511","1461":"1461","1581":"1581","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","after 1510":"1510 jälkeen","England":"England","Shenstone, Staffordshire, England":"Shenstone, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Middleton, Warwickshire, England":"Middleton, Warwickshire, England"},"fr":{"1470–after 1510":"1470–après 1510","1461–1510":"1461–1510","1486–1558":"1486–1558","1490–1554":"1490–1554","1511–1581":"1511–1581","1470–1510":"1470–1510","1558":"1558","1511":"1511","1554":"1554","1510":"1510","1486":"1486","about 1511":"environ 1511","1461":"1461","1581":"1581","1470":"1470","1490":"1490","after 1510":"après 1510","England":"Angleterre","Shenstone, Staffordshire, England":"Shenstone, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Middleton, Warwickshire, England":"Middleton, Warwickshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice Clarkson est née en 1470, à Middleton, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille avec William Rugeley. Elle est décédée après 1510."},"de":{"1470–after 1510":"1470–nach 1510","1461–1510":"1461–1510","1486–1558":"1486–1558","1490–1554":"1490–1554","1511–1581